ratings.question_text: Overall, how would you rate the workload of this course in comparison to other Yale courses you have taken?
What is your overall assessment of this course?
Do you expect to use this class for credit toward your major, or toward a pre-professional program?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I would recommend this lab to anyone who needs labs for pre-med or the major. It's a pretty relaxing experience, and also interesting. It compliments the lecture course very well, betterthan any lab I have ever taken.

This was a very interesting lab. I think it really helped explain concepts of the class. Though the class periods were often long, the out of class work was very manageable. A very good way to fulfill lab requirements.
This was a good lab. It was a little stressful because sometimes it can be very hard to collect data; however, you're allowed to share with other groups, so that helps a lot. Generally a good course.

Yes! As far as biology labs go, this one is relatively relaxed and doesn't have long lab reports and you still learn a lot. You get to work with invertebrates like earthworms, drosophila, frogs, and grasshoppers and learn some basic electrophysiology techniques that are a good supplement to the lecture topics. Many of the experiments are a wonderful hands-on demonstration of phenomenon discussed in class especially if you are interested in neurotransmission or visual transduction.
